<subSubSection id="C36CDAD58D34FFFAB5EAFB1BFD26FAB1" box="[151,708,1266,1293]" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BC9895E8D34FFFAB5EAFB1BFD26FAB1" blockId="12.[151,1437,1266,2013]" box="[151,708,1266,1293]" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">
<heading id="D0813E328D34FFFAB5EAFB1BFD26FAB1" bold="true" box="[151,708,1266,1293]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D34FFFAB5EAFB1BFD26FAB1" bold="true" box="[151,708,1266,1293]" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">
Untangling the 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D34FFFAB42DFB1AFDE2FAB1" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[336,512,1267,1293]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D34FFFAB42DFB1AFDE2FAB1" bold="true" box="[336,512,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">Lysmata vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36CDAD58D34FFFBB5EAFAFEFD42FE35" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="202" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC9895E8D34FFFAB5EAFAFEFA92FA7D" blockId="12.[151,1437,1266,2013]" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">
Due to the great morphological variability within the 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D34FFFAB787FAFEFC83FA8C" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[762,865,1303,1328]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D34FFFAB787FAFEFC83FA8C" box="[762,865,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex, absence of 
<typeStatus id="54CD37FC8D34FFFAB127FAFEFB68FA8D" box="[1114,1162,1303,1329]" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">type</typeStatus>
material, and history of doubtful records of this species, we applied an integrative analysis to delimit the putative species within the complex and resolve the taxonomic status of 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D34FFFAB718FAB6FD5BFAC5" authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" box="[613,697,1375,1401]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D34FFFAB718FAB6FD5BFAC5" box="[613,697,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D34FFFAB78CFAB6FC7AFAC5" authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1921" box="[753,920,1375,1401]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Hippolysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="durbanensis">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D34FFFAB78CFAB6FC7AFAC5" box="[753,920,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">L. durbanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Our integrated morphological and molecular data strongly support the hypothesis that 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D34FFFAB722FA6AFD26FA20" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[607,708,1411,1436]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D34FFFAB722FA6AFD26FA20" box="[607,708,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A231E8378D34FFFAB7B7FA6AFCDBFA21" box="[714,825,1411,1437]" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" sensu="lato">sensu lato</taxonomicNameLabel>
is comprised of six taxonomic entities (including three undescribed species) with important morphological and distributional differences among constituent members.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC9895E8D34FFFAB5BAFA22FBA0F925" blockId="12.[151,1437,1266,2013]" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">
We noted clear and consistent morphological and color pattern differences among various members of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D34FFFAB0FBFA22FF3DF9B4" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D34FFFAB0FBFA22FF3DF9B4" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex that were further supported by molecular analyses. Most strikingly was the absence of both an accessory branch (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D34FFFAB412F9FAFE37F990" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[367,469,1555,1580]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D34FFFAB412F9FAFE37F990" box="[367,469,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[clade LV1] and 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D34FFFAB7E1F9FAFCA6F991" authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1921" box="[668,836,1555,1581]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Hippolysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="durbanensis">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D34FFFAB7E1F9FAFCA6F991" box="[668,836,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">L. durbanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and pleonal red transverse bands in 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D34FFFAB190F9FAFAB6F990" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1261,1364,1555,1580]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D34FFFAB190F9FAFAB6F990" box="[1261,1364,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, compared with a one-segmented accessory branch observed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D34FFFAB65CF9DEFC96F9ED" authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" box="[801,884,1591,1617]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D34FFFAB65CF9DEFC96F9ED" box="[801,884,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(clade LV4) and 
<emphasis id="B902554C8D34FFFAB149F9DEFBA9F9EC" box="[1076,1099,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">L.</emphasis>
sp. AUS2 (clade LV3) and the presence of pleonal transverse bands in 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D34FFFAB732F9B2FD40F9C9" authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" box="[591,674,1627,1653]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D34FFFAB732F9B2FD40F9C9" box="[591,674,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We also observed important differences in the number of carpal and meral segments of the second pereopod, particularly between 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D34FFFAB631F996FC53F924" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[844,945,1663,1688]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D34FFFAB631F996FC53F924" box="[844,945,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D34FFFAB69AF996FBD9F925" authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" box="[999,1083,1663,1689]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D34FFFAB69AF996FBD9F925" box="[999,1083,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC9895E8D34FFFAB5BAF94AFDF0F805" blockId="12.[151,1437,1266,2013]" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">
<materialsCitation id="3B1E83038D34FFFAB5BAF94AFDFFF95D" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3804716301" collectionCode="ASAP" location="Further" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" specimenCount="1">
<location id="8EA9DF858D34FFFAB5BAF94AFEF9F901" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DF38488D34FFFBB5EAFB1BFD42FE35:8EA9DF858D34FFFAB5BAF94AFEF9F901" box="[199,283,1699,1725]" name="Further" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">Further</location>
, our phylogeny recovered five strongly supported and divergent clades, (fig. 4), which were also delineated as putative species by 
<collectionCode id="ED67119B8D34FFFAB4ABF92EFDFFF95D" box="[470,541,1735,1761]" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">ASAP</collectionCode>
</materialsCitation>
<materialsCitation id="3B1E83038D34FFFAB759F92EFDECF805" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3804716303" collectionCode="ABGD" country="United States of America" county="Automatic Barcode Gap Discovery" location="Taiwan" municipality="These" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" specimenCount="2">
and included LV1 (the eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F361C9CE8D34FFFAB602F92EFC58F95D" box="[895,954,1735,1761]" name="United States of America" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">USA</collectingCountry>
, Hong Kong [
<typeStatus id="54CD37FC8D34FFFAB125F92EFB69F95D" box="[1112,1163,1735,1761]" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">type</typeStatus>
locality], 
<collectingCountry id="F361C9CE8D34FFFAB183F92EFA7AF95D" box="[1278,1432,1735,1761]" name="New Zealand" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
, and 
<location id="8EA9DF858D34FFFAB5B4F902FEC2F8BA" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DF38488D34FFFBB5EAFB1BFD42FE35:8EA9DF858D34FFFAB5B4F902FEC2F8BA" box="[201,288,1771,1798]" country="United States of America" county="Automatic Barcode Gap Discovery" municipality="These" name="Taiwan" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">Taiwan</location>
), LV2 (a single individual from northern Australia), LV3 (northern 
<collectingCountry id="F361C9CE8D34FFFAB157F902FB77F8BA" box="[1066,1173,1771,1798]" name="Australia" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">Australia</collectingCountry>
), LV4 (Panama, 
<collectingCountry id="F361C9CE8D34FFFAB025F902FA7EF8B9" box="[1368,1436,1771,1797]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">Brazil</collectingCountry>
[
<typeStatus id="54CD37FC8D34FFFAB5E3F8E6FF33F895" box="[158,209,1807,1833]" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">type</typeStatus>
locality], Thailand, and 
<collectingCountry id="F361C9CE8D34FFFAB490F8E6FD94F895" box="[493,630,1807,1833]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
), and LV5 (a single individual identified as “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D34FFFAB1FDF8E6FB0AF894" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1152,1256,1807,1832]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D34FFFAB1FDF8E6FB0AF894" box="[1152,1256,1807,1832]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” from 
<location id="8EA9DF858D34FFFAB040F8E6FA7BF895" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DF38488D34FFFBB5EAFB1BFD42FE35:8EA9DF858D34FFFAB040F8E6FA7BF895" box="[1341,1433,1807,1833]" country="United States of America" county="Automatic Barcode Gap Discovery" municipality="These" name="Xiamen" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">Xiamen</location>
, China). 
<location id="8EA9DF858D34FFFAB58DF8DAFEA5F8F1" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DF38488D34FFFBB5EAFB1BFD42FE35:8EA9DF858D34FFFAB58DF8DAFEA5F8F1" box="[240,327,1843,1869]" country="United States of America" county="Automatic Barcode Gap Discovery" municipality="These" name="Genetic" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">Genetic</location>
differences were extremely wide, with minimum inter-clade genetic distances (
<emphasis id="B902554C8D34FFFAB1C4F8DAFB25F8F0" box="[1209,1223,1843,1868]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">p</emphasis>
-distances) ranging from 0.048 (LV3 vs. LV4) to 0.430 (LV2 vs. LV5). 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BAD13248D34FFFAB7ADF8BEFCF1F8CD" box="[720,787,1879,1905]" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">These</collectingMunicipality>
findings are bolstered by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7F4AF8D34FFFAB14FF8BEFAFBF8CD" author="Aguilar, R. &amp; Prakash, S. &amp; Ogburn, M. B. &amp; Lohan, K. M. P. &amp; MacDonald III, K. S. &amp; Driskell, A. C. &amp; Ahyong, S. T. &amp; Leray, M. &amp; McIlroy, S. E. &amp; Tuckey, T. D. &amp; Baeza, J. A." box="[1074,1305,1879,1905]" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" pagination="1" refId="ref16244" refString="Aguilar, R., Prakash, S., Ogburn, M. B., Lohan, K. M. P., MacDonald III, K. S., Driskell, A. C., Ahyong, S. T., Leray, M., McIlroy, S. E., Tuckey, T. D. &amp; Baeza, J. A. (2022) Unresolved taxonomy can confounds invasive species identification: the Lysmata vittata (Stimpson, 1860) (Decapoda: Caridea: Lysmatidae) species complex and recent introduction of Lysmata vittata sensu stricto in the western Atlantic. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 42 (1). https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / jcbiol / ruab 079" type="journal article" year="2022">
Aguilar 
<emphasis id="B902554C8D34FFFAB1F3F8BEFB24F8CD" box="[1166,1222,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">et al.</emphasis>
(2022)
</bibRefCitation>
, which also recovered four similar strongly supported clades and were all delimited as putative species using 
<collectingCounty id="62A8F1D28D34FFFAB1BEF892FEA2F805" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">Automatic Barcode Gap Discovery</collectingCounty>
analysis (
<collectionCode id="ED67119B8D34FFFAB4CDF876FDE4F805" box="[432,518,1951,1977]" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">ABGD</collectionCode>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC9895E8D34FFFBB5BAF82AFD42FE35" blockId="12.[151,1437,1266,2013]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1436,151,393]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="202" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">
The fixing of a 
<typeStatus id="54CD37FC8D34FFFAB408F82AFE2CF861" box="[373,462,1987,2013]" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">neotype</typeStatus>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7F4AF8D34FFFAB488F82AFD3CF861" author="Aguilar, R. &amp; Prakash, S. &amp; Ogburn, M. B. &amp; Lohan, K. M. P. &amp; MacDonald III, K. S. &amp; Driskell, A. C. &amp; Ahyong, S. T. &amp; Leray, M. &amp; McIlroy, S. E. &amp; Tuckey, T. D. &amp; Baeza, J. A." box="[501,734,1987,2013]" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" pagination="1" refId="ref16244" refString="Aguilar, R., Prakash, S., Ogburn, M. B., Lohan, K. M. P., MacDonald III, K. S., Driskell, A. C., Ahyong, S. T., Leray, M., McIlroy, S. E., Tuckey, T. D. &amp; Baeza, J. A. (2022) Unresolved taxonomy can confounds invasive species identification: the Lysmata vittata (Stimpson, 1860) (Decapoda: Caridea: Lysmatidae) species complex and recent introduction of Lysmata vittata sensu stricto in the western Atlantic. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 42 (1). https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / jcbiol / ruab 079" type="journal article" year="2022">
Aguilar 
<emphasis id="B902554C8D34FFFAB72FF82AFD68F861" box="[594,650,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">et al.</emphasis>
(2022)
</bibRefCitation>
, provided the necessary criteria to define 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D34FFFAB1CDF82AFAF7F860" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1200,1301,1987,2012]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D34FFFAB1CDF82AFAF7F860" box="[1200,1301,1987,2012]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="201">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with major morphological characters including: 1) uniramous dorsal antennule; 2) rostrum reaching distal end of second antennular article; 3) scaphocerite overreaching the end of the antennular peduncle; 4) stylocerite reaching the mid-length of the first antennular article; 5) presence of a pterygostomial spine; 6) 8–13 meral segments of the second pereopod; 7) 18–23 carpal segments of the second pereopod; and 8) coloration pattern consisting of numerous longitudinal red stripes without dark transverse bands on the pleon. These important morphological criteria provided a framework to delimit the putative species within the 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D35FFFBB731FEA2FD51FED8" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[588,691,331,356]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D35FFFBB731FEA2FD51FED8" box="[588,691,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="202">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex using integrative taxonomic methods, helping to settle over a century of taxonomic uncertainty.
</paragraph>
